<H1><CENTER>1995 George Washington Fellows Program <BR>
Final Report</CENTER>
</H1>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<H3>From July 3-28, 1995, Discovery Institute held the second annual George
Washington Fellows Program in Religion and Public Life. Eight students selected
from colleges and universities around the nation participated in the program,
which was led by Dr. John West, Senior Fellow at Discovery Institute and
director of the Institute's program on <A HREF="religion.html">Religion,
Liberty &amp; Civic Life</A>. The late Kathryn Flower was program assistant.
(Biographies of the 1995 Fellows are included.)</H3>
